{{- define "integration-fix" -}}
{{- if .IntegrationFix}}

=== INTEGRATION FIX MODE ===
This task failed to merge due to conflicts with the integration branch.
Your worktree is clean (any prior failed rebase was aborted).
Resolve the conflicts, verify tests pass, then submit.

WORKFLOW:

1. FETCH AND REBASE
   git -C {{.Worktree}} fetch {{.ProjectRoot}} {{.IntegrationBranch}}
   git -C {{.Worktree}} rebase FETCH_HEAD

2. RESOLVE CONFLICTS (git pauses at each conflict)
   For each conflicted file:
     a. Read the file — resolve conflict markers (<<<<<<<, =======, >>>>>>>)
     b. Preserve both your changes and integration branch changes
     c. git -C {{.Worktree}} add <resolved-file>
   Then: git -C {{.Worktree}} rebase --continue
   Repeat until rebase completes.

3. IF UNRESOLVABLE
   git -C {{.Worktree}} rebase --abort
   Use {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_mark_blocked: {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}", "reason": "Merge conflicts require redesign: <explain>", "questions": ["..."]}

4. VALIDATE
   Run tests in the worktree. Verify done_when criteria still met.

5. SUBMIT
   Get SHA: git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD
   Use {{.ToolPrefix}}liza_submit_for_review: {"task_id": "{{.TaskID}}", "commit_sha": "<SHA from above>", "agent_id": "{{.AgentID}}"}
{{- end}}
{{- end -}}
